Class SparseSampledContinuousFunction

  • java.lang.Object

      • uk.co.saiman.data.SparseSampledContinuousFunction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ContinuousFunction, RegularSampledContinuousFunction, SampledContinuousFunction, uk.co.strangeskies.mathematics.expression.Expression<ContinuousFunction,ContinuousFunction>, uk.co.strangeskies.mathematics.expression.SelfExpression<ContinuousFunction>, uk.co.strangeskies.utilities.Copyable<ContinuousFunction>, uk.co.strangeskies.utilities.Observable<ContinuousFunction>, uk.co.strangeskies.utilities.Self<ContinuousFunction>

    public class SparseSampledContinuousFunction
extends uk.co.strangeskies.mathematics.expression.ImmutableExpression<ContinuousFunction,ContinuousFunction>
implements RegularSampledContinuousFunction
    A (currently) immutable implementation of RegularSampledContinuousFunction which optimises memory usage for sampled continua with mostly 0 sample values in the codomain.

        Instantiate based on the given significant sample indices and intensities. Samples at indices other than those given are assumed to be of intensity 0 in the codomain.
        Parameters:
        frequency - The number of samples per unit in the domain
        depth - The number of conceptual samples, starting from 0
        samples - The number of non-zero samples
        indices - The sequential indices of non-zero samples
        intensities - The intensities at the given non-zero sample indices

        Sometimes it is useful to linearise a continuous function in order to perform complex processing, or for display purposes. This method provides a linear view of any continuous function. Implementations may remove features which are unresolvable at the given resolution.
